changelog.comment: Initial entry. Reviewer 1 re-drew reaction SMARTS and SMILES to make them RDKit-compatible.

reactions.description: Methylates the N-terminus of the vancomycin backbone. Substrate specificity not known in detail. SMARTS has been designed to be not too unspecific by accident. True substrate specificity might be broader than assumed here.
Substrate specificity not known in detail. SMARTS has been designed to be not too unspecific by accident. True substrate specificity might be broader than assumed here.
Reaction from demethyl-vancomycin to dimethyl-vancomycin. Vancomycin is usually only monomethylated.
